Jim TillerSHOW VISIONSHOW BIO
I have a fundamental passion for security and all things about security. Moreover, I’m passionate about innovative approaches to security that materially improves the capabilities of businesses and individuals to protect themselves. Either through process improvement, technology advancements, or compelling practices, things that make security interesting and effective capture my attention. This is absolutely the case with Automate. Innovative technology, fresh and compelling approach to a very old and persistent challenge, and tangibly improves security. What’s not to get passionate about?Jim is a proven security leader with over two decades of information security experience.He has a history of outstanding performance and growth, business turnarounds, and global recognition for innovation in security strategies and execution.Jim is a published, internationally-recognized expert on information security. He is currently with Optiv as the VP and GM of their security programs. Prior to Optiv he was with HP as the Global Security Practice Head and with British Telecom as the VP of Security Services for North America and the VP of Ethical Hacking for BT.Prior to that was the Chief Security Officer for International Network Services, where he created the highest NSA rated professional security services organization in the world. From 1999 to 2002, he worked at Bell Labs for the advancement of security technologies. With Bell Labs, he led the development of a communications systems security architecture that resulted in a patent and is the X.805 ITU standard.Jim is based on North Carolina with his family and is a contributor to the Green Beret Foundation and H3 in support of our wounded, ill, and injured warriors.Jaideep KrishnaSHOW VISIONSHOW BIO
