I have a passion for all things technology and its impact on business and society.  I believe identity and security are the core elements underlying and enabling the trust frameworks we take for granted today.  Maintaining these trust frameworks is more important today than ever before and is a base requirement for businesses to thrive as they become ever more entrusted with their customer’s information.  In this digital era, Authomate provides government, businesses, employees, and consumers simple, innovative identity and security management solutions ensuring only those who need access get it.  I’m excited to support the leadership team on Authomate’s future success.Ian M. Klein is President of Atlas Mobility International, a newly formed entity focused on developing and guiding global growth opportunities in the technology space.  Ian currently advises several companies in the technology sector addressing the Internet of Things, Data Protection, Identity, Security, Education, and Finance. Formerly, Ian spent over nine years with GSMA, where he held several positions in commercialization, innovation, strategy, and corporate development.  Prior to his departure in late 2015, he was GSMA's Head of Corporate Business Development, leading a team focused on GSMA’s strategic growth, commercial industry partnerships in the wireless ecosystem, and formulating approaches to help drive mobile technology adoption and growth.  From 2007 until 2009, Ian was GSMA’s Mobile Innovation Director responsible for improving GSMA’s and the mobile industry’s connection to the venture capital and entrepreneur ecosystems worldwide. Prior to his time at GSMA, Ian spent fifteen years in early growth stages of the personal computer sector, mergers & acquisitions consulting, communications technology strategy, portfolio management, and international business and partnership development. Ian is known globally for his principled approach, the breadth and depth of his business knowledge, and his ability to simultaneously focus on long term impacts while executing in the moment.
 
The goal of being security can only be achieved by significantly hindering the offenders, attackers, and hackers. You can rarely remove human error, so the question is how can you prioritize the other areas of security and reduce risk. Authentication, over and over again, it ranked the highest risk area, least expensive to improve, and provides the highest return in terms of dollars spent to risk reduced. Simplicity is key to success, and I see Authomate as that magical missing link between user experience, improved security, lower risk and being extremely cost effective.


Doug is globally recognized security executive with over twenty-five years of leadership experience with service providers that deliver security and risk management services to enterprises, service providers and government organizations.
